  "local_port": 39018,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If your seat on a train booked through the PRS (Passenger Reservation System) remains waitlisted even after the departure of the train, you are not allowed to board the train using that ticket. In such cases, Indian Railways has a policy for refunds on waitlisted tickets.\n\n### Refund Policy for Waitlisted Tickets:\n1. **If the ticket remains waitlisted even after the chart preparation:**\n   - You are eligible for a **full refund**, excluding the service charge (if applicable).\n   - The refund is processed automatically after the departure of the train. It is credited back to the original payment method (e.g., bank account, credit card, etc.).\n\n2. **Refund Process:**\n   - No manual action is required for the refund. It is processed by the Indian Railways system.\n   - The refund is typically processed within **3\u20137 working days**, depending on your bank or payment gateway.\n\n3. **Service Charges:**\n   - If you booked the ticket online, a minimal service charge (if applicable) is deducted from the refund.\n   - For tickets booked at the counter, no service charge is deducted.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Boarding the Train:** You **cannot board the train** if your ticket remains waitlisted after chart preparation.\n- **Partially Confirmed Tickets:** If some passengers on your ticket are confirmed and others are waitlisted, only the waitlisted passengers are not allowed to board. Confirmed passengers can travel as per their status.\n\nTo check the refund status, you can visit the **IRCTC website** or contact their customer care. For tickets booked at the counter, you may need to visit the PRS counter for further assistance.\n\nLet me know if you have more questions!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
